channel.title: 1.3 Route Table :: Deploy TensorFlow model on AWS with EC2 and Docker
channel.description: A route table contains a set of rules, called routes, that determine where network traffic from your subnet or gateway is directed. Create Route Table At the VPC management console: Click Route tables. Click Create route table. At the Create route table page, enter the following information: Name tag: route-table-inference-1. VPC: Choose the VPC with tag vpc-inference-1. Click Create route table. After the route table is created, you will need to associate it to the public subnet.
